{"title": "Linjiang Yalu River Bridge\n", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linjiang_Yalu_River_Bridge", "tags": ["Category:1938 establishments in China", "Category:1938 establishments in Korea", "Category:All articles with unsourced statements", "Category:Baishan", "Category:Bridges completed in 1938", "Category:Bridges in China", "Category:Bridges in North Korea", "Category:Buildings and structures in Chagang Province", "Category:Buildings and structures in Jilin", "Category:China\u2013North Korea border crossings", "Category:International bridges", "Category:Manchukuo", "Category:Transport in Jilin", "Category:Yalu River"], "text": "The Linjiang Yalu River Bridge (Chinese: \u4e34\u6c5f\u56fd\u9645\u5927\u6865) is a bridge over the Yalu River, connecting Linjiang City, Jilin Province, China, with Chunggang County, Chagang Province, North Korea. It was built by the Japanese in 1938 and Linjiang Border Post is located there. A little downstream from the bridge is Yunfeng Dam.\nDuring the Korean War, it was one of the border posts from which the Chinese People's Volunteer Army entered North Korea.\n\nSee also\nSino\u2013Korean Friendship Bridge and New Yalu River Bridge (Dandong)\nJi'an Yalu River Border Railway Bridge\nChangbai-Hyesan International Bridge\nTumen Border Bridge (Tumen City)\nTumen River Bridge (Hunchun)\n\n\n== References =="}